<title>USA: Computer Associates Q4 earnings summary.</title>
<headline>Computer Associates Q4 earnings summary.</headline>
<dateline>ISLANDIA, N.Y. 1997-05-21</dateline>
<text>
<p>1997			1996</p>
<p> Shr profit		 $0.90   profit	 $0.70</p>
<p> Net profit	     336,008   profit     265,099</p>
<p> Revs		   1,205,061		1,110,422</p>
<p> Avg shrs		 374,998		  380,036</p>
<p>		 Year</p>
<p> Shr profit		 $0.97     loss	 $0.16</p>
<p> Net profit	     365,941     loss	56,354</p>
<p> Revs		   4,040,248		3,504,629</p>
<p> Avg shrs		 379,183		  362,268</p>
<p>(All data above 000s except per share numbers)</p>
<p>NOTES: Quarters and fiscal years ended March 31.</p>
<p>FY 1997 includes a $598 million writeoff associated with the acquisition of Cheyenne Software Inc. Without this charge, earnings would have been $963.9 million, or $2.54 per share.</p>
<p>FY 1996 includes a $1.3 billion writeoff associated with the acquisition of Legent Corp.  Without this charge earnings would have been $751.7 million, or $1.99 per share.</p>
<p>All share amounts adjusted for two stock splits in 1996.</p>
<p>Full name of company is Computer Associates International Inc.</p>
